le=Clarke is a bisexual character.|url=https://twitter.com/JRothenbergTV/status/570775409643532288|publisher=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=2 May 2017|date=26 February 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n|''[[Banana (TV series)|Banana]]''<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk\">{{cite web|title=Freddie Fox: 'I am very ambitious. I have a voracious appetite'|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/11351180/Freddie-Fox-I-am-very-ambitious.-I-have-a-voracious-appetite.html|accessdate=14 March 2016}}</ref>\n| Freddie Baxter\n| Described by roommate Dean Monroe as being \"kind of anything\" in reference to his sexuality.<ref name=\"Episode 1\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 1|series=Cucumber|network=Channel 4|date=22 January 2015|season=1|number=1}}</ref> He is confirmed as being bisexual by actor Freddie Fox.<ref name=\"Kinsella\">{{cite web|last=Kinsella|first=Felicity|title=cucumber, banana, tofu's freddie fox on gay shame, gay pride and avoiding labelling|url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_au/article/cucumber-banana-tofus-freddie-fox-on-gay-shame-gay-pride-and-avoiding-labelling|work=i-D|date=19 January 2015|accessdate=2015-02-08}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014\u20132017\n|''[[Black Sails (TV series)|Black Sails]]''\n|Eleanor Guthrie<br />Anne Bonny\n|Eleanor was in a relationship with a woman, Max, at the beginning of the first season.\n\nAnne Bonny has a fusional relationship with Jack Rackham but falls in love with Max in season 2.\n|-\n| 2014\u20132019\n|''[[Broad City]]''\n| Ilana Wexler<br />Abbi Abrams\n| Throughout the series, Ilana has relationships with men, women and non-binary people, and she regularly makes her feelings towards Abbi known. In season 2 she enters a relationship with a woman who looks identical to her. Abbi has relationships with men exclusively until the final season, in which she begins dating a female doctor.\n\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n|''[[Chasing Life]]''\n| Brenna Carver\n| A 16-year-old girl who develops feelings for both Kieran, a boy she met in the aftermath of a party, and Greer, a classmate who is an out lesbian. After quickly coming to terms with her simultaneous feelings for both, she attempts to maintain romantic relationships with the two. Although initially reluctant to assign labels to herself, she eventually comes to self-identify as bisexual.\n|-\n| 2015\u20132017\n|''[[Code Black (TV series)|Code Black]]''\n| Noa Kean\n| Mentions having dated both boys and girls.\n|-\n| 2015\u2013present\n|''[[Crazy Ex-Girlfriend (TV series)|Crazy Ex-Girlfriend]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=The CW's Crazy Ex-Girlfriend Fights Bisexual Erasure with \"Gettin' Bi\"|url=http://www.themarysue.com/crazy-ex-girlfriend-gettin-bi/|accessdate=14 March 2016}}</ref>\n| Darryl Whitefeather <br />Valencia Perez <br/>Maya\n| Previously divorced from a woman. Upon hanging out with Rebecca and her friends, he starts developing a crush on White Josh. After White Josh kisses him on the cheek, Darryl begins to questioning his sexuality, eventually realizing during a cardio class that he is attracted to both genders. He proudly exclaims to White Josh that he is a \"both-sexual\", and the two of them begin dating.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.vulture.com/2016/02/crazy-ex-girlfriend-darryl-white-josh.html|title = Crazy Ex-Girlfriend's Darryl Is TV's Most Darling Bisexual|website = Vulture|access-date = 2016-03-03}}</ref>\nMaya comes out as bisexual in solidarity with Darryl.<br/>\nValencia began the series in a relationship with Josh Chan, ended the series in a relationship with Beth and was revealed to have had an almost-romance with Father Brah in high school. \n\n|-\n| 2015\n|''[[Cucumber (TV series)|Cucumber]]''<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk\" />\n| Freddie Baxter\n| Described by roommate Dean Monroe as being \"kind of anything\" in reference to his sexuality.<ref name=\"Episode 1\" /> He is confirmed as being bisexual by actor Freddie Fox.<ref name=\"Kinsella\" />\n|-\n|2015\n| ''[[Other Space]]''\n| Stewart Lipinski\n| Stewart pines after his female crewmate 