he show in season 3, sleeping with Sara later that episode, and continues to flirt with Gary later on in future episodes. His relationship with a man, Dez, is a major part of his motives in season 4, where he's a regular. <br /> Gary has shown his attraction to John Constantine, a man, on several occasions, as well as his attraction to Ava and Mona, two women.\n|-\n| 2014\u20132019\n|''[[Gotham (TV series)|Gotham]]''\n|[[Barbara Kean]]\n| Has a bisexual relationship with Major Crimes Division Officer [[Renee Montoya]] and fianc\u00e9 [[James Gordon (Gotham)|Jim Gordon]].\n|-\n| 2014\u20132017\n|''[[Halt and Catch Fire (TV series)|Halt and Catch Fire]]''\n| Joe MacMillan\n| Initiates a season-long sexual relationship with female programmer Cameron Howe in episode 1. In episode 3, seduces the trophy boyfriend of wealthy widow in order to avoid a business deal with her. In episode 7, his ex-boyfriend Simon re-enters his life briefly to inform Joe he has [[AIDS]].\n|-\n| 2014\u2013present\n|''[[How to Get Away with Murder]]''\n|[[Annalise Keating]]\n| Annalise kisses her ex-girlfriend Eve Rothlow in Season 2. It is later revealed that they were in a serious relationship during law school. They briefly rekindle their relationship, until Eve finishes her case in Philadelphia and needs to return home.\n|-\n|2016\u2013present\n|''[[The Loud House]]''\n|Luna Loud\n|Seen having a crush on a girl in the second season, after having a crush on a boy in the first season.\n|-\n| 2016\u2013present\n|''[[Lucifer (TV series)|Lucifer]]''\n|[[Lucifer (DC Comics)|Lucifer Morningstar]]\n| In episode 2, Lucifer wakes up in bed with women and a man. In season 2 episode 11, when being interrogated, one of his male exes discussed their sexual relations.\n|-\n| 2015\u20132019\n|''[[Mr. Robot]]''\n| Tyrell Wellick<br />Dominique DiPierro<br />Darlene Alderson<br />Angela Moss<br />Shayla Nico<br />Others\n| Although married to Joanna, Tyrell seduces his boss' male secretary in order to find out who the new CTO candidate is. He's in love with Eliott.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.com/mr-robot-creator-sam-esmail-confirms-tyrell-loves-elliot-teases-season-3-details-2420904|title='Mr. Robot' Creator Sam Esmail Confirms 'Tyrell Loves Elliot,' Teases Season 3 Details|last=AM|first=Jordianne Cornejo 09/23/16 AT 6:09|date=2016-09-23|website=International Business Times|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref><br />Agent Dominique DiPierro refers to heterosexual relationships prior to her introduction to the series and continues to engage in heterosexual fantasy multiple times via IRC chats. However, throughout the series she engages exclusively in homosexual physical relationships and expresses a desire to no longer be with men.<br />Darlene Alderson begins the series in an complicated relationship with her boyfriend and engages in repeated casual intercourse with a businessman. Later in the series she develops a relationship with DiPierro.<br />Angela Moss and Shayla Nico are only seen in heterosexual sexual relationships throughout the series, but briefly engage in kissing on another, suggesting that they are more flexible in their sexuality outside of this interaction.<br />Other non-consentual homosexual activity is suggested throughout the series from characters who are presumed to be straight. This includes attempted male on male rape in a prison setting and Elliot Alderson's childhood molestation by his father. \n|-\n| 2014\u20132016\n|''[[Penny Dreadful (TV series)|Penny Dreadful]]''\n|[[Dorian Gray]]<br />[[Ethan Chandler]]\n| Sexuality in Victorian era portrayed as having more freedom. Showrunner [[John Logan (writer)|John Logan]] perceives sexuality as fluid and has implied that all characters could potentially be depicted as such.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Diaz|first1=Eric|title=Penny Dreadful Comic-Con 2014 Panel Report|url=http://www.nerdist.com/2014/07/penny-dreadful-comic-con-2014-panel-report/|website=Nerdist|accessdate=13 August 2014|archive-url=http